## 2. Why Qwen2.5-0.5B Is a Strong Target

Qwen2.5-0.5B is a good public demo target because:

* it is small enough to run on consumer hardware;
* it is part of a well-known model family;
* it is structurally related to larger Qwen models, making projection more plausible than cross-family extreme transfers;
* it has existing vLLM validation coverage in Neural-Scalpel;
* SQL/Coding tasks produce clear before/after examples.

Qwen2.5-0.5B has a documented 32,768-token context length in its Hugging Face model card, and Qwen2.5-0.5B-Instruct belongs to the Qwen2.5 family of 0.5B to 72B instruction/base models. Qwen2.5-Coder-7B-Instruct is a code-focused Qwen-family model with long-context support up to 128K tokens. ([Hugging Face][1])

Qwen’s official Qwen2.5 announcement states that open-source Qwen2.5 models, except the 3B and 72B variants, are licensed under Apache 2.0, but every source model, target model, and adapter must still be checked individually before redistribution. ([Qwen][2])

