Spider is suitable for text-to-SQL evaluation because it is a cross-domain benchmark with complex SQL over multiple databases, and its evaluation scripts support exact, component, and execution-based metrics. ([yale-lily.github.io][3])

### Evaluation Modes

Run:

```text
Base target
Projected route
Source adapter/model reference, optional
Native LoRA baseline if available
```

### Required Metrics

SQL:

```text
syntax_validity_rate
execution_accuracy
exact_match
component_match
format_compliance
```

Coding:

```text
