## 17. Recommended Implementation Order

### Phase QSQL-A: Source Selection

```text
Pick source SQL/Coding adapter.
Check license.
Check module names and shapes.
```

### Phase QSQL-B: Payload Projection

```text
Generate Qwen2.5-0.5B-compatible payload.
Run static integrity checks.
```

### Phase QSQL-C: Qualitative Smoke

```text
Run 20 curated before/after prompts.
Select 5 best and 5 failure cases.
```

### Phase QSQL-D: Metric Evaluation

```text
Run 50–200 SQL/Coding prompts.
Compute syntax validity, execution accuracy, judge preference.
```

### Phase QSQL-E: Runtime Safety

```text
Run route application / rollback / determinism checks.
```

### Phase QSQL-F: HF Packaging

```text
Write model card.
Upload payload if license permits.
Upload reports.
Link GitHub.
```

### Phase QSQL-G: Launch

```text
Post on X / Reddit / HF community / Zenn / Qiita.
Use “adapter behavior survival test” framing.
```

